      {
        "id": 2616833,
        "name": "Joshua Kates",
        "username": "Joshua_Kates",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/e47774/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-04-07T18:23:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"151258\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Buzz and I split a small stash years ago. I got the corked ones and he got the good ones. Somehow this good one slipped into my grasp. Lovely nose of beetroot and forest floor, the fruit was dark cherry, at first a bit sour but cleaned up nicely, 93 acids well-integrated, tannins resolved. Lots of sediment.  A real nice bottle.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>93\u2019s are the best drinking 90\u2019s burgs I\u2019ve been encountering of late, definitely for white and I think also for red (better than '90, '96 and even '99, which does not seem to me ready). This was just the villages bottling I presume? So only 23 more years for my '16\u2019s I guess.</p>",
        "post_number": 3,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
